5895
5896 /// Gets the type pointed to by this ObjC pointer. Always returns non-null.
5897 ///
5898 /// This method is equivalent to getPointeeType() except that
5899 /// it discards any typedefs (or other sugar) between this
5900 /// type and the "outermost" object type. So for:
5901 /// \code
5902 /// \@class A; \@protocol P; \@protocol Q;
5903 /// typedef A<P> AP;
5904 /// typedef A A1;
5905 /// typedef A1<P> A1P;
5906 /// typedef A1P<Q> A1PQ;
5907 /// \endcode
5908 /// For 'A*', getObjectType() will return 'A'.
5909 /// For 'A<P>*', getObjectType() will return 'A<P>'.
5910 /// For 'AP*', getObjectType() will return 'A<P>'.
5911 /// For 'A1*', getObjectType() will return 'A'.
5912 /// For 'A1<P>*', getObjectType() will return 'A1<P>'.
5913 /// For 'A1P*', getObjectType() will return 'A1<P>'.
5914 /// For 'A1PQ*', getObjectType() will return 'A1<Q>', because
5915 /// adding protocols to a protocol-qualified base discards the
5916 /// old qualifiers (for now). But if it didn't, getObjectType()
5917 /// would return 'A1P<Q>' (and we'd have to make iterating over
5918 /// qualifiers more complicated).

5999 using qual_range = llvm::iterator_range<qual_iterator>;
6000

6021 }

6023 bool isSugared() const { return false; }
6024 QualType desugar() const { return QualType(this, 0); }
6025
6026 /// Retrieve the type of the superclass of this object pointer type.

6122/// A qualifier set is used to build a set of qualifiers.
6123class QualifierCollector : public Qualifiers {
6124public:
6125 QualifierCollector(Qualifiers Qs = Qualifiers()) : Qualifiers(Qs) {}
6126
6127 /// Collect any qualifiers on the given type and return an
6128 /// unqualified type. The qualifiers are assumed to be consistent
6129 /// with those already in the type.
6130 const Type *strip(QualType type) {
6131 addFastQualifiers(type.getLocalFastQualifiers());
6132 if (!type.hasLocalNonFastQualifiers())
6133 return type.getTypePtrUnsafe();
6134
6135 const ExtQuals *extQuals = type.getExtQualsUnsafe();
6136 addConsistentQualifiers(extQuals->getQualifiers());
6137 return extQuals->getBaseType();
6138 }
6139
6140 /// Apply the collected qualifiers to the given type.
6141 QualType apply(const ASTContext &Context, QualType QT) const;
6142
6143 /// Apply the collected qualifiers to the given type.
6144 QualType apply(const ASTContext &Context, const Type* T) const;
6145};

6295/// Determine whether this type is more
6296/// qualified than the Other type. For example, "const volatile int"
6297/// is more qualified than "const int", "volatile int", and
6298/// "int". However, it is not more qualified than "const volatile
6299/// int".
6300inline bool QualType::isMoreQualifiedThan(QualType other) const {
6301 Qualifiers MyQuals = getQualifiers();
6302 Qualifiers OtherQuals = other.getQualifiers();
6303 return (MyQuals != OtherQuals && MyQuals.compatiblyIncludes(OtherQuals));
6304}
6305
6306/// Determine whether this type is at last
6307/// as qualified as the Other type. For example, "const volatile
6308/// int" is at least as qualified as "const int", "volatile int",
6309/// "int", and "const volatile int".
6310inline bool QualType::isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(QualType other) const {
6311 Qualifiers OtherQuals = other.getQualifiers();
6312
6313 // Ignore __unaligned qualifier if this type is a void.
6314 if (getUnqualifiedType()->isVoidType())
6315 OtherQuals.removeUnaligned();
6316
6317 return getQualifiers().compatiblyIncludes(OtherQuals);
6318}

6320/// If Type is a reference type (e.g., const
6321/// int&), returns the type that the reference refers to ("const
6322/// int"). Otherwise, returns the type itself. This routine is used
6323/// throughout Sema to implement C++ 5p6:
6324///
6325/// If an expression initially has the type "reference to T" (8.3.2,
6326/// 8.5.3), the type is adjusted to "T" prior to any further
6327/// analysis, the expression designates the object or function
6328/// denoted by the reference, and the expression is an lvalue.
6329inline QualType QualType::getNonReferenceType() const {
6330 if (const auto *RefType = (*this)->getAs<ReferenceType>())
6331 return RefType->getPointeeType();
6332 else
6333 return *this;
6334}

6351/// Tests whether the type is categorized as a compound type.
6352///
6353/// \returns True for types specified in C++0x [basic.compound].
6354inline bool Type::isCompoundType() const {
6355 // C++0x [basic.compound]p1:
6356 // Compound types can be constructed in the following ways:
6357 // -- arrays of objects of a given type [...];
6358 return isArrayType() ||
6359 // -- functions, which have parameters of given types [...];
6360 isFunctionType() ||
6361 // -- pointers to void or objects or functions [...];
6362 isPointerType() ||
6363 // -- references to objects or functions of a given type. [...]
6364 isReferenceType() ||
6365 // -- classes containing a sequence of objects of various types, [...];
6366 isRecordType() ||
6367 // -- unions, which are classes capable of containing objects of different
6368 // types at different times;
6369 isUnionType() ||
6370 // -- enumerations, which comprise a set of named constant values. [...];
6371 isEnumeralType() ||
6372 // -- pointers to non-static class members, [...].
6373 isMemberPointerType();
6374}

6673inline bool Type::isIntegerType() const {

6676 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::Int128;
6677 if (const EnumType *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType)) {
6678 // Incomplete enum types are not treated as integer types.
6679 // FIXME: In C++, enum types are never integer types.
6680 return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl()) &&
6681 !IsEnumDeclScoped(ET->getDecl());
6682 }
6683 return false;
6684}

6686inline bool Type::isFixedPointType() const {
6687 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType)) {
6688 return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortAccum &&
6689 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatULongFract;
6690 }
6691 return false;
6692}
6693
6694inline bool Type::isFixedPointOrIntegerType() const {
6695 return isFixedPointType() || isIntegerType();
6696}

6698inline bool Type::isSaturatedFixedPointType() const {
6699 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType)) {
6700 return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortAccum &&
6701 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatULongFract;
6702 }
6703 return false;
6704}
6705
6706inline bool Type::isUnsaturatedFixedPointType() const {
6707 return isFixedPointType() && !isSaturatedFixedPointType();
6708}
6709
6710inline bool Type::isSignedFixedPointType() const {
6711 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType)) {
6712 return ((BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortAccum &&
6713 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::LongAccum) ||
6714 (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::ShortFract &&
6715 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::LongFract) ||
6716 (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortAccum &&
6717 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatLongAccum) ||
6718 (BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::SatShortFract &&
6719 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::SatLongFract));
6720 }
6721 return false;
6722}
6723
6724inline bool Type::isUnsignedFixedPointType() const {
6725 return isFixedPointType() && !isSignedFixedPointType();
6726}
6727
6728inline bool Type::isScalarType() const {
6729 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
6730 return BT->getKind() > BuiltinType::Void &&
6731 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::NullPtr;
6732 if (const EnumType *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType))
6733 // Enums are scalar types, but only if they are defined. Incomplete enums
6734 // are not treated as scalar types.
6735 return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl());
6736 return isa<PointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
6737 isa<BlockPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
6738 isa<MemberPointerType>(CanonicalType) ||
6739 isa<ComplexType>(CanonicalType) ||
6740 isa<ObjCObjectPointerType>(CanonicalType);
6741}
6742
6743inline bool Type::isIntegralOrEnumerationType() const {
6744 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
6745 return BT->getKind() >= BuiltinType::Bool &&
6746 BT->getKind() <= BuiltinType::Int128;
6747
6748 // Check for a complete enum type; incomplete enum types are not properly an
6749 // enumeration type in the sense required here.
6750 if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(CanonicalType))
6751 return IsEnumDeclComplete(ET->getDecl());
6752
6753 return false;
6754}

6756inline bool Type::isBooleanType() const {
6757 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CanonicalType))
6758 return BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Bool;
6759 return false;
6760}

6763 auto *DT = getContainedDeducedType();
6764 return DT && !DT->isDeduced();
6765}

6787inline const Type *Type::getBaseElementTypeUnsafe() const {
6788 const Type *type = this;
6789 while (const ArrayType *arrayType = type->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
6790 type = arrayType->getElementType().getTypePtr();

6796 if (type->isAnyPointerType())

6798 else if (type->isArrayType())
6799 return type->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();

6839// Helper class template that is used by Type::getAs to ensure that one does
6840// not try to look through a qualified type to get to an array type.
6841template <typename T>
6842using TypeIsArrayType =
6843 std::integral_constant<bool, std::is_same<T, ArrayType>::value ||
6844 std::is_base_of<ArrayType, T>::value>;
6845
6846// Member-template getAs<specific type>'.
6847template <typename T> const T *Type::getAs() const {
6848 static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value,
6849 "ArrayType cannot be used with getAs!");
6850
6851 // If this is directly a T type, return it.
6852 if (const auto *Ty = dyn_cast<T>(this))
6853 return Ty;
6854
6855 // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
6856 if (!isa<T>(CanonicalType))
6857 return nullptr;
6858
6859 // If this is a typedef for the type, strip the typedef off without
6860 // losing all typedef information.
6861 return cast<T>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
6862}
6863
6864template <typename T> const T *Type::getAsAdjusted() const {
6865 static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value, "ArrayType cannot be used with getAsAdjusted!");
6866
6867 // If this is directly a T type, return it.
6868 if (const auto *Ty = dyn_cast<T>(this))
6869 return Ty;
6870
6871 // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
6872 if (!isa<T>(CanonicalType))
6873 return nullptr;
6874
6875 // Strip off type adjustments that do not modify the underlying nature of the
6876 // type.
6877 const Type *Ty = this;
6878 while (Ty) {
6879 if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Ty))
6880 Ty = A->getModifiedType().getTypePtr();
6881 else if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<ElaboratedType>(Ty))
6882 Ty = E->desugar().getTypePtr();
6883 else if (const auto *P = dyn_cast<ParenType>(Ty))
6884 Ty = P->desugar().getTypePtr();
6885 else if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<AdjustedType>(Ty))
6886 Ty = A->desugar().getTypePtr();
6887 else if (const auto *M = dyn_cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Ty))
6888 Ty = M->desugar().getTypePtr();
6889 else
6890 break;
6891 }
6892
6893 // Just because the canonical type is correct does not mean we can use cast<>,
6894 // since we may not have stripped off all the sugar down to the base type.
6895 return dyn_cast<T>(Ty);
6896}
6897
6898inline const ArrayType *Type::getAsArrayTypeUnsafe() const {
6899 // If this is directly an array type, return it.
6900 if (const auto *arr = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(this))
6901 return arr;
6902
6903 // If the canonical form of this type isn't the right kind, reject it.
6904 if (!isa<ArrayType>(CanonicalType))
6905 return nullptr;
6906
6907 // If this is a typedef for the type, strip the typedef off without
6908 // losing all typedef information.
6909 return cast<ArrayType>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
6910}
6911
6912template <typename T> const T *Type::castAs() const {
6913 static_assert(!TypeIsArrayType<T>::value,
6914 "ArrayType cannot be used with castAs!");
6915
6916 if (const auto *ty = dyn_cast<T>(this)) return ty;
6917 assert(isa<T>(CanonicalType));
6918 return cast<T>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
6919}
6920
6921inline const ArrayType *Type::castAsArrayTypeUnsafe() const {
6922 assert(isa<ArrayType>(CanonicalType));
6923 if (const auto *arr = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(this)) return arr;
6924 return cast<ArrayType>(getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
6925}

6928 QualType CanonicalPtr)
6929 : AdjustedType(Decayed, OriginalType, DecayedPtr, CanonicalPtr) {

6937QualType DecayedType::getPointeeType() const {
